        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="286"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                <head>286. Telegram From the Station in Iran to the Central Intelligence Agency<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d286fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency.
                        Secret; Operational Immediate. Transcribed specifically for the <hi
                            rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi> series from microfilm in the
                        Central Intelligence Agency that no longer exists. See “Sources”
                        chapter.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Tehran</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-19"
                        >August 19, 1953</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_TEHE_1">TEHE</gloss> 742. 1. Overthrow of <persName
                        corresp="#p_MM_1">Mossadeq</persName> appears on verge of success. <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZA_1">Zahedi</persName> now at radio station.</p>
                <p>2. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HLW_1">Henderson</persName> and I request
                    urgently that five million dollars be held immediately available to support new
                        <gloss target="#t_govt_1">govt</gloss> and enable it meet <gloss
                        target="#t_govt_1">govt</gloss> payroll. Will advise later how money should
                    be deposited but see no need ship money out here.</p>
                <p>End of message.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
